{"TopicId":150487,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"Problem with Normal Maps","CreatedByName":"Shatten","CreatedById":163415,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-21T08:29:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Shatten","CreatedById":163415,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-21T08:29:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello all!\u003Cbr\u003E\nThere is a question of the normals maps:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow exactly do you make normal maps in the game?\u003Cbr\u003E\nI make them like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hRhsSLrQcC0.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://pp.vk.me/c626226/v626226901/2b0f2/hRhsSLrQcC0.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0cards normal, then there is a problem with the light\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222016-10-20.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-lw4FJ0b7E9U/WAkLKoqyp-I/AAAAAAAADwA/G1XPvik-l6k92VXoddVkBP0y-j0jArOZACL0B/h256/2016-10-20.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks Unity normally makes a height map (I guess) in the alpha channel\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223QSgegPkkqQ.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://pp.vk.me/c626226/v626226901/2b0f9/3QSgegPkkqQ.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n. \u00A0KS accepts these cards, but there is an example where the normal map works in its expected form. These normal maps work well\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sojkNoy9bYM.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://pp.vk.me/c626226/v626226901/2b10a/sojkNoy9bYM.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use a shader KSP\u00A0/ Bumped\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for attention\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-21T08:39:59Z\u0022 title=\u002210/21/2016 08:39  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 21, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Shatten\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"InsaneDruid","CreatedById":137849,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-21T10:10:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t really understand your question, as I don\u0027t know what you mean with \u0022cards\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour normal map seem ok-ish on that image. The alpha channel of the diffuse texture is usually interpreted as a specular map. not a height map. But this only is needed in ksp_specular or ksp_bumped_specular. For ksp_bumped your diffuse texture should be 24bit, without an alpha channels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shatten","CreatedById":163415,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-21T12:38:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuestion was that if I used the normal map RGB\u00A0on items are placed correctly the shadows from the light\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222016-10-20.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-lw4FJ0b7E9U/WAkLKoqyp-I/AAAAAAAADwA/G1XPvik-l6k92VXoddVkBP0y-j0jArOZACL0B/h256/2016-10-20.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n. The problem was solved renaming file name added at the end of \u0022_NRM\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}